The discussion reference page is <http://www.gnu.org/software/hurd/help.html>

See also the [[HurdIRC]] topic.

## <a name="Mailing_Lists"> Mailing Lists </a>

* [debian-hurd](http://www.debian.org/MailingLists/subscribe) and web [archives](http://lists.debian.org/debian-hurd/) - general system discussion, packaging, integration

* [help-hurd](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/help-hurd) and web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/help-hurd/)
* [bug-hurd](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/bug-hurd) and web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/bug-hurd/) - technical debugging and discussion
* [thug](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/thug) and web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/thug/) - Toronto-area Hurd Users Group and discussion
* [hurd-devel-readers](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/hurd-devel-readers) and hurd-devel web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/hurd-devel/) - serious technical debugging and discussion
  * The main list is hurd-devel. It has the archives but the subscriptions are restricted. You are welcome to subscribe to hurd-devel-readers however to avoid duplication the archives for this list are turned off.
* [web-hurd](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/web-hurd) and web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/web-hurd/) - discussion of web pages at <http://hurd.gnu.org>
* [l4-hurd](http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/l4-hurd) and web [archives](http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/l4-hurd/) - theoretical kernel development

    P.S.
       There does not exist any "stupid" questions!
       We have all been beginners.
